WEBVTT

00:02.001 --> 00:03.771
[STATIC BUZZING]

00:03.937 --> 00:05.705
REPORTER 1: A powerful
new strain of influenza

00:05.839 --> 00:08.442
has killed more
than 5,000 people in Egypt,

00:08.609 --> 00:10.511
according to reports out
of Cairo.

00:13.881 --> 00:15.316
REPORTER 2:
New cases of Saharan flu

00:15.449 --> 00:19.187
were reported in France,
Spain, Germany, and Italy.

00:22.356 --> 00:23.457
REPORTER 3:
The flu is spreading

00:23.624 --> 00:25.526
beyond doctors' abilities
to contain it.

00:30.198 --> 00:31.899
REPORTER 1: The flu
has reached U.S. shores,

00:32.031 --> 00:33.067
with cases reported in...

00:33.334 --> 00:34.335
REPORTER 2: We have reports
that a million

00:34.468 --> 00:35.636
have died in the Middle East.

00:36.270 --> 00:37.638
REPORTER 1:
...and San Francisco.

00:43.211 --> 00:45.579
REPORTER 2: We have reports
that a million have died...

00:45.713 --> 00:47.615
[INDISTINCT TRANSMISSIONS]

00:54.988 --> 00:56.290
REPORTER 1:
The World Health Organization

00:56.524 --> 00:58.726
warns that this could be
a civilization-ending event.

00:58.859 --> 01:00.428
REPORTER 2: ...this could be
a civilization-ending event.

01:05.199 --> 01:07.235
Riots are breaking out
across the country,

01:07.368 --> 01:09.403
as people desperately try
to secure

01:09.537 --> 01:11.272
life-support bunkers
for their families.

01:11.405 --> 01:13.407
To ensure survival
of the human race.

01:16.544 --> 01:18.912
The World Health Organization
has started construction

01:19.046 --> 01:21.249
on half a million
underground bunkers.

01:26.754 --> 01:28.789
Scientists are searching
desperately for a cure,

01:28.922 --> 01:31.125
but they warn
that Saharan flu mortality

01:31.259 --> 01:33.461
could be 100 percent.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.733
REPORTER 1: Authorities promise
lottery winners

01:39.867 --> 01:42.770
will have access to bunkers
within 24 hours.

01:43.171 --> 01:44.071
REPORTER 2: ...survive.

01:47.408 --> 01:50.278
With an estimated
three billion dead worldwide,

01:50.411 --> 01:53.347
it is unclear if the bunkers
will be finished in time.

01:57.385 --> 01:59.119
Authorities promise
lottery winners

01:59.253 --> 02:02.456
will have access to bunkers
within 24 hours.

02:06.794 --> 02:08.429
REPORTER 1:
This is our final broadcast.

02:09.396 --> 02:11.665
Good luck, and Godspeed.

02:19.340 --> 02:21.275
[OVERLAPPING TRANSMISSIONS]

02:29.183 --> 02:30.651
ATLANTA:
I'm thoroughly disgusted.

02:30.784 --> 02:32.686
I-- I don't even know
if I can look at you the sa--

02:32.820 --> 02:34.588
Cool it! You're gonna
give yourself a stroke.

02:34.788 --> 02:36.089
And at your age, Atlanta,
you need

02:36.224 --> 02:37.791
-to take care of yourself.
-You seem very calm

02:37.925 --> 02:39.793
for someone who just confessed
to murder.

02:39.927 --> 02:42.296
ORLANDO: I mean, I get bored.
I do-- I do some bad shit.

02:42.430 --> 02:43.464
Ain't never hurt none of y'all.

02:43.764 --> 02:44.965
You've hurt us now.
Now we can't pretend

02:45.098 --> 02:46.767
-you're not such a bad guy.
-Come on.

02:47.568 --> 02:48.869
-You knew I was a bad guy.
-Right.

02:49.002 --> 02:49.903
But now we can't pretend--

02:50.137 --> 02:51.239
You know,
I'm-- I'm almost flattered

02:51.372 --> 02:52.706
by that, Denver, but, honestly,

02:52.840 --> 02:54.342
I could care less
what you think.

02:54.475 --> 02:55.743
You couldn't care less.

02:56.344 --> 02:57.478
-What?
-DENVER: The phrase,

02:57.711 --> 02:59.280
it's you couldn't care less.

02:59.880 --> 03:02.049
Saying you could care less means
that you actually care.

03:02.182 --> 03:03.684
Well, how
about I don't give a rat's ass?

03:03.817 --> 03:05.219
-You like that, Denver?
-That's actually better.

03:05.519 --> 03:06.720
-Congratulations.
-You starting shit

03:06.854 --> 03:08.188
just for kicks, Orlando?

03:09.089 --> 03:10.291
That's classy, man.
Keeping it mature.

03:10.424 --> 03:11.825
What, you think I'm here
to entertain y'all?

03:11.959 --> 03:13.494
Nah. Just think
you're one fucked-up dude.

03:13.627 --> 03:15.229
You sure you're not talking
about yourself there, hombre?

03:15.363 --> 03:17.365
[CHUCKLES]
Hey, only God can judge us, man.

03:17.631 --> 03:20.200
You know, I've been staring
at your boring, mopey faces

03:20.334 --> 03:23.337
on this little digital box
for half a decade.

03:23.871 --> 03:25.706
I mean, it's time for a change,
right?

03:25.973 --> 03:28.008
Some truth, some honesty.

03:28.141 --> 03:30.177
[SIGHS] You don't give a shit
about honesty.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.945
You just like the sound
of your own voice.

03:32.145 --> 03:33.414
ORLANDO: That hurts me, Chicago.

03:33.881 --> 03:35.082
I value honesty.

03:36.183 --> 03:37.985
It's what separates the men
from children.

03:38.118 --> 03:39.520
Hmm, real men don't lie.
Is that it?

03:39.653 --> 03:40.821
ORLANDO: Yeah,
that's what little, uh,

03:41.188 --> 03:43.156
pissy babies like you say,
right?

03:43.824 --> 03:45.326
That's why you're a child...

03:46.159 --> 03:47.027
and I'm a man.

03:47.160 --> 03:48.529
You never did fit in with us.

03:49.330 --> 03:52.099
-[SCOFFS] This explains so much.
-Ah, that really means a lot

03:52.232 --> 03:53.767
coming from you there, Atlanta.

03:53.934 --> 03:55.436
I mean, there's no way
in hell you could survive

03:55.569 --> 03:57.905
-out there in the real world.
-We are all survivors.

03:58.038 --> 03:59.707
I'm talking about living
in the shit.

03:59.873 --> 04:01.241
Atlanta here,
she ain't never lived

04:01.375 --> 04:02.410
-in no shit!
-It's no excuse

04:02.610 --> 04:04.812
-for what you've done.
-But least I own it!

04:04.945 --> 04:06.414
How many people
have you killed, anyway?

04:06.547 --> 04:08.516
Ah, to be honest, 15.

04:08.649 --> 04:10.217
I don't know. Maybe 20,
if you want to be real.

04:10.351 --> 04:13.086
-Oh, my God.
-"Oh, my God." Are you serious?

04:13.253 --> 04:15.889
Come on. Most of them
were bank robberies gone bad.

04:16.423 --> 04:17.725
Okay, I'm sorry. Hold on.

04:18.257 --> 04:21.028
There was a time that I did it
for sport,

04:21.228 --> 04:23.764
and to tell you the truth,
it was actually fun.

04:24.932 --> 04:27.901
I am trying to find a way
to pray for your soul...

04:28.702 --> 04:30.270
but I'm not even sure
if you have one.

04:30.404 --> 04:32.806
Oh, and this is coming
from the mother of the year.

04:33.441 --> 04:35.075
What's it like to, uh,

04:35.208 --> 04:36.810
think about those three
precious angels

04:36.944 --> 04:39.547
up there,
dead with everyone else?

04:40.080 --> 04:42.249
-How dare you?
-No, I mean, I'm just asking.

04:42.383 --> 04:43.617
I mean, they were--
They were kids, right?

04:44.251 --> 04:46.487
I mean,
that is a hell of a way to go,
especially being so young.

04:46.620 --> 04:47.721
Dude!

04:47.921 --> 04:49.222
Too far, man. That's fucked up.

04:49.357 --> 04:51.825
But that's what I'm talking
about. It's the truth!

04:52.125 --> 04:55.095
Hey, the truth!
And none of you want to hear it!

04:55.228 --> 04:57.264
You know what? You're right.

04:58.499 --> 05:01.669
I don't want to hear it.
[CRYING]

05:02.235 --> 05:03.837
I have a proposal
for the Domain.

05:03.971 --> 05:06.474
Oh, here it comes,
the bullshit democracy.

05:06.607 --> 05:08.376
Since day one,
Orlando's been nothing

05:08.509 --> 05:10.944
but a thorn in our sides
and now he's confessing

05:11.078 --> 05:12.513
to brutally murdering
innocent people.

05:12.646 --> 05:13.847
No, no, no.
They weren't all innocent.

05:13.981 --> 05:15.282
We don't have
to listen to it anymore.

05:15.449 --> 05:17.918
We can just ban him
and shut off his feed for good.

05:18.051 --> 05:21.021
Ah! I love it! You can't ban me.

05:21.622 --> 05:23.591
-[TUTS] I can.
-HOUSTON: For real?

05:24.091 --> 05:25.659
You can just shut us off
at any time?

05:25.826 --> 05:27.495
It's not that simple, okay?

05:27.628 --> 05:28.862
It's-- It's a hack I came across

05:28.996 --> 05:30.464
after studying the code
for years,

05:30.598 --> 05:32.966
but that doesn't mean
I agree with Boston.

05:33.434 --> 05:34.868
Banning someone is permanent.

05:35.369 --> 05:37.505
We can't come back from it,
so we have to make sure

05:37.638 --> 05:39.306
that this is something
we all wanna do.

05:39.440 --> 05:41.274
So that's why we vote.
It's what we do.

05:41.409 --> 05:43.444
Oh, this-- This here,
is a frigging joke.

05:43.577 --> 05:46.113
I have to listen
to this blah-blah-blah bullshit,

05:46.246 --> 05:47.114
day in and day out.

05:47.247 --> 05:48.682
Banning me is not a punishment.

05:48.816 --> 05:50.651
Orlando, banning you
is permanent.

05:51.619 --> 05:53.286
No contact with anybody

05:53.421 --> 05:54.622
for the rest
of your time down here.

05:54.755 --> 05:56.189
That could mean
more than 20 years.

05:56.323 --> 05:59.226
Well, that to me, sounds
like a 20-year vacation.

05:59.993 --> 06:03.063
Who votes to ban Orlando
from the Domain?

06:03.230 --> 06:04.164
I do.

06:04.698 --> 06:07.367
-Me.
-We need one more. Phoenix?

06:09.336 --> 06:11.639
-This feels wrong.
-Be reasonable.

06:11.772 --> 06:13.240
-It's extreme.
-He's extreme.

06:15.342 --> 06:18.011
-No, I can't do it.
-Come on.

06:18.145 --> 06:20.681
He could be alone for decades.
It's not fair.

06:20.814 --> 06:22.382
Maybe he deserves it.

06:23.316 --> 06:26.386
I'm sorry. I can't sign off
on this. No. I vote no.

06:27.154 --> 06:29.523
Denver, I'm assuming
you're voting with Phoenix.

06:30.023 --> 06:31.525
Yes, I am.

06:32.359 --> 06:33.561
That's two against three.

06:34.662 --> 06:37.097
Houston... you're it.
What's it gonna be?

06:37.230 --> 06:39.266
Ah, fuck, man, I don't--
I don't wanna be the last vote.

06:39.399 --> 06:40.734
-You gotta do it.
-HOUSTON: Shit.

06:42.202 --> 06:44.071
I can't, man. I ca--
I can't vote.

06:44.538 --> 06:46.373
You know, let me make this easy
for all of you.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.375
Do it.

06:49.142 --> 06:51.979
-Ban me.
-Wow. I wasn't expecting that.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.346
Shut him down.

06:53.747 --> 06:55.348
No, I won't do it
until Phoenix says it's okay.

06:55.483 --> 06:57.951
It's not up to her. We voted.
It's over.

06:58.085 --> 06:59.587
He's right, Denver.
It's not up to me.

07:00.287 --> 07:02.590
Unplug it, Denver.

07:05.258 --> 07:06.794
Did I ever tell you guys
I'm a psychic?

07:07.761 --> 07:09.963
I could read minds
and the future.

07:10.097 --> 07:11.765
You want me to tell you
what the future holds

07:11.899 --> 07:14.968
-for all of you?
-Denver, unplug him now.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.039
Pain and suffering,

07:19.372 --> 07:21.208
a life of shit
like you could never imagine,

07:21.341 --> 07:22.643
nothing but pure misery.

07:22.776 --> 07:25.879
And you know what really--
[CHUCKLES] It pisses me off,

07:26.213 --> 07:28.415
because I'm not gonna be here
to witness it.

07:33.721 --> 07:34.588
Done.

07:35.656 --> 07:36.590
Amen.

08:10.758 --> 08:11.859
DENVER: You awake?

08:17.931 --> 08:18.866
Yeah.

08:32.613 --> 08:33.581
How you feeling?

08:36.316 --> 08:37.450
Pretty restless.

08:38.552 --> 08:41.688
[SIGHS] Yeah. Today was, uh,
was rough.

08:42.623 --> 08:43.557
PHOENIX: Mm-hmm.

08:46.994 --> 08:48.095
Did you agree with me?

08:50.130 --> 08:51.031
Yeah, of course.

08:52.633 --> 08:55.002
I wouldn't have done it
unless you said it was okay.

08:56.003 --> 08:56.904
I know.

08:59.973 --> 09:02.442
But did you actually agree
with my point?

09:03.510 --> 09:04.578
Yeah. I mean, I was...

09:06.046 --> 09:07.815
I was torn. You know, I can see

09:07.948 --> 09:09.316
where the others
are coming from.

09:09.717 --> 09:11.018
People make mistakes.

09:11.885 --> 09:13.386
We've all made mistakes.

09:13.687 --> 09:15.188
So no one
should ever be punished?

09:15.623 --> 09:17.725
I'm not saying that, no.

09:19.627 --> 09:21.361
I guess
I just don't feel comfortable...

09:21.995 --> 09:22.863
judging.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.666
You gotta remember, Phoenix,
he's not dead.

09:26.199 --> 09:30.403
Okay? He's still in a bunker
in Florida in some marsh,

09:30.738 --> 09:34.441
spouting his redneck bullshit
philosophies to himself,

09:34.574 --> 09:36.543
so don't lose
too much sleep over it.

09:37.177 --> 09:39.780
And who knows? This could
be over in a year, right?

09:40.714 --> 09:41.581
Wouldn't even matter.

09:42.282 --> 09:43.751
That would be so nice.

09:44.918 --> 09:47.120
[SIGHS]
Do you ever think about just

09:47.254 --> 09:48.722
what it would be like to...

09:49.690 --> 09:51.291
be in the same room together...

09:52.559 --> 09:54.061
all the time?

09:55.295 --> 09:57.631
No more... screens...

09:58.531 --> 09:59.767
be able to touch you?

10:00.233 --> 10:02.002
[SIGHS]

10:03.436 --> 10:05.238
-Never.
-Mm.

10:06.039 --> 10:08.108
-[LAUGHS]
-PHOENIX: Of course I do.

10:10.377 --> 10:12.379
It's what keeps me
looking forward to the future.

10:14.514 --> 10:15.615
[SIGHS]

10:18.018 --> 10:19.086
I love you, Phoenix.

10:21.722 --> 10:22.723
I love you, too.

10:30.764 --> 10:32.666
[MACHINE BEEPING]

11:28.856 --> 11:30.357
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

11:56.817 --> 11:59.019
[TOILET FLUSHES]

12:12.032 --> 12:14.034
AUTOMATED FEMALE VOICE:
Please dispense Supplival.

12:20.707 --> 12:22.742
Please dispense Supplival.

12:32.385 --> 12:34.221
Supplival dispensed.

12:54.474 --> 12:57.010
[CONTROLLED BREATHING]

12:59.579 --> 13:02.249
-[ROWING MACHINE WHIRRING]
-[BIRDS CHIRPING]

13:05.886 --> 13:07.287
[DENVER SIGHS]

13:10.323 --> 13:11.491
-DENVER: Morning.
-Hey.

13:12.960 --> 13:15.595
-Did you sleep okay?
-Not really.

13:18.231 --> 13:19.666
Was it another dream
about your mom?

13:22.535 --> 13:23.503
BOSTON: What about your mom?

13:23.703 --> 13:25.605
Well, thank you
for interrupting, Boston.

13:25.738 --> 13:26.639
Morning to you, too, Denver.

13:26.974 --> 13:28.341
You know, do you ever consider--
I don't know,

13:28.475 --> 13:31.111
maybe not barging in
on a private conversation?

13:31.244 --> 13:32.779
BOSTON: Hey, if you two have
a secret to share,

13:32.913 --> 13:34.314
you can always start
your own chat room.

13:34.614 --> 13:36.249
Common feed is fair game.

13:40.387 --> 13:42.789
[SIGHS]
Oh, wow.

13:44.091 --> 13:45.225
This migraine.

13:45.358 --> 13:47.394
Eighty percent
of migraines result

13:47.527 --> 13:50.563
-from dehydration.
-That statistic reeks of B.S.

13:50.763 --> 13:51.865
-Can you prove me wrong?
-DENVER: Yeah,

13:51.999 --> 13:53.066
but I don't have time.

13:54.167 --> 13:55.368
[BLOWS KISS]

13:55.768 --> 13:57.137
Good morning, angels.

13:59.139 --> 14:00.307
Mommy has a headache.

14:00.773 --> 14:01.975
HOUSTON: Fuck, man!

14:02.475 --> 14:05.078
Fuck! This sleep cycle's
fucking bullshit!

14:10.283 --> 14:11.751
BOSTON:
Look what the cat dragged in.

14:11.952 --> 14:14.354
Get off my back, Boston.
Slept like shit.

14:14.487 --> 14:16.323
If I didn't know any better,
I'd say you looked hung over.

14:16.489 --> 14:17.724
Man, I wish.

14:17.991 --> 14:19.859
Uh, wow,
like a couple of bottles

14:19.993 --> 14:21.494
and some bitches, shit.

14:21.628 --> 14:23.897
We could have ourselves
a party, right, Atlanta?

14:24.031 --> 14:26.199
You know what, Houston?
I'm not even gonna dignify that

14:26.333 --> 14:28.969
-with a response.
-Aw, you love me.

14:30.870 --> 14:32.139
Oh, fuck!

14:32.672 --> 14:35.042
God, I hope this fucking shit
doesn't keep up.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.576
You can't sleep,
put a blanket over your head.

14:36.709 --> 14:38.311
Fuck, I'll put a blanket
over your mom's head.

14:38.445 --> 14:39.412
The sleep cycle

14:39.779 --> 14:40.847
doesn't just affect
the lighting, okay?

14:40.981 --> 14:42.349
It--
It affects your inner clock.

14:42.482 --> 14:45.552
-Yeah, what Denver said.
-Oh, yeah, I forgot.

14:45.718 --> 14:48.621
Denver is the resident expert
on everything.

14:48.755 --> 14:51.358
-Well, you said it, not me.
-Chicago.

14:52.159 --> 14:54.427
-Nice of you to join us.
-Give me a break.

14:55.595 --> 14:56.563
Think I have a cold.

14:56.930 --> 14:59.399
You're in a hermetically
sealed environment, so...

15:00.367 --> 15:01.601
that's actually,
physically impossible.

15:01.734 --> 15:03.270
Well,
something's making me sick.

15:03.403 --> 15:04.904
Maybe you should drink
a fucking Supplival,

15:05.038 --> 15:06.406
get some meat
on your weak-ass bones.

15:06.539 --> 15:07.907
-Back off.
-All this doom and gloom.

15:08.041 --> 15:10.577
Everybody cheer up.
We're alive another day.

15:11.211 --> 15:12.912
-Happy now?
-Oui, monsieur.

15:13.913 --> 15:15.548
Phoenix, you still working
on your French?

15:16.049 --> 15:17.884
Oui. C'est bien. Et tu?

15:18.151 --> 15:21.955
Uh, les chatons son...

15:23.256 --> 15:24.157
mignons?

15:24.524 --> 15:26.226
Did you just say that kittens
are cute?

15:26.359 --> 15:28.595
That's, um,
not what I meant to say.

15:28.728 --> 15:30.297
-Well, what did you mean to say?
-Doesn't really matter.

15:30.430 --> 15:31.931
-I'm still learning.
-You know, you've been learning

15:32.065 --> 15:33.900
for two years now

15:34.067 --> 15:36.069
-with no visible progress.
-Denver.

15:36.203 --> 15:37.404
I don't study every day.

15:37.604 --> 15:39.306
-This is just for fun.
-I'm sure that's why you do it.

15:39.439 --> 15:40.307
What's that supposed to mean?

15:41.041 --> 15:42.809
While you two are busy bickering
like an old married couple,

15:42.942 --> 15:44.644
I'm gonna go ahead
and do my morning prayers.

15:45.612 --> 15:46.579
Anybody care to join?

15:46.846 --> 15:48.648
Every morning
you ask us if we wanna pray

15:48.781 --> 15:50.483
and the answer is always
the same.

15:50.617 --> 15:52.319
Isn't that the definition
of psychosis?

15:52.619 --> 15:53.586
I'll pray with you.

15:54.087 --> 15:55.155
-Really?
-PHOENIX: Sure.

15:55.588 --> 15:57.190
I don't know any prayers,
though.

15:57.457 --> 15:59.192
That's okay.
Uh, I can send you one.

16:00.293 --> 16:03.196
-[KEYPAD TYPING]
-[BEEPING]

16:03.763 --> 16:06.499
It's one that, uh,
I used to do with my girls

16:06.633 --> 16:08.001
just before I put them to bed.

16:08.835 --> 16:09.769
Got it?

16:10.903 --> 16:11.871
-Yep.
-ATLANTA: Okay.

16:13.406 --> 16:15.775
-O Lord, make me brave.
-Make me brave.

16:17.177 --> 16:19.279
BOTH:
Brave enough to face the dark,

16:20.247 --> 16:22.515
the dark that works
to pull me in.

16:24.051 --> 16:25.818
As the storm rages through...

16:26.953 --> 16:30.390
let me rise above the gale
with bright eyes,

16:31.091 --> 16:33.693
confident Thy way is wise.

16:34.561 --> 16:36.763
Lord, make me brave...

16:37.830 --> 16:40.700
brave to face the murk of life.

16:41.934 --> 16:43.870
Help me with my human plight.

16:44.904 --> 16:47.274
Help me to retain my sight...

16:48.441 --> 16:50.843
to know that from the dark
comes light.

16:52.312 --> 16:55.315
To know that
from the dark comes light.

16:56.649 --> 16:58.685
-ATLANTA: Amen.
-Amen.

17:00.687 --> 17:02.689
Thanks, Phoenix. That was nice.

17:02.822 --> 17:05.358
Very nice. Touching, even.

17:05.492 --> 17:07.060
All right, everybody,
let's get ready for the day.

17:07.194 --> 17:08.361
[CLAPS]
Morning reports, let's hear 'em.

17:08.528 --> 17:10.896
Okay, the Network neutralized

17:11.030 --> 17:13.766
almost three billion
Saharan flu particles overnight.

17:13.900 --> 17:17.404
That's a .009 increase
from yesterday.

17:18.070 --> 17:20.607
A slight uptick.
That's the good news.

17:21.473 --> 17:24.377
Bad news is that works out
to about 19 years

17:24.644 --> 17:27.414
-before total containment.
-Oh, God damn!

17:27.547 --> 17:29.416
I hope that shit picks up
the pace, man.

17:29.549 --> 17:30.650
Well, there was that one night

17:30.950 --> 17:31.918
where it jumped up
a whole percentage point.

17:32.051 --> 17:33.353
Atlanta's on the right track.

17:33.986 --> 17:35.155
We have to stay optimistic

17:35.388 --> 17:36.889
because we do not know
what's gonna happen tomorrow.

17:37.023 --> 17:38.891
Probably nothing,
just like yesterday

17:39.025 --> 17:40.993
and the day before that,
day before that,

17:41.461 --> 17:42.429
Atlanta, you're up.

17:42.562 --> 17:44.764
Okay,
so blood scans look normal.

17:45.532 --> 17:47.434
Except, Phoenix,
your pressure's up.

17:47.834 --> 17:49.736
-Are you okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

17:49.969 --> 17:50.970
Maybe I'm not reading it right,

17:51.138 --> 17:52.572
but your brain scan
looks kinda weird.

17:52.705 --> 17:54.207
Maybe someone else should, uh,

17:54.341 --> 17:55.875
-read the brain scan.
-Hey, man, fuck you.

17:56.008 --> 17:57.444
-I can read this.
-Just had a bad dream,

17:57.577 --> 17:59.712
and I'm feeling kind of out
of it. It's probably just that.

18:00.046 --> 18:01.248
Was the bad dream
about your mom?

18:01.848 --> 18:03.250
I'd rather not talk
about it right now.

18:03.383 --> 18:05.952
-Jesus, Boston.
-I'm sorry.

18:06.953 --> 18:09.956
-Wow, that was-- That was rude.
-Anyway, moving on.

18:11.258 --> 18:15.662
Bunker population is 489,573,

18:15.795 --> 18:18.931
which is down eight
from yesterday.

18:19.065 --> 18:20.099
That's not good.

18:20.433 --> 18:22.735
-It's probably just a bad night.
-This is so stupid.

18:23.136 --> 18:24.471
We're all looking
at the same numbers

18:24.604 --> 18:26.306
on this tiny, little screen.

18:26.573 --> 18:28.107
Why are we pretending
like we have separate jobs?

18:28.241 --> 18:30.109
Because we have to keep focused.

18:30.243 --> 18:32.545
Each one of us has one statistic
to keep an eye on.

18:32.679 --> 18:33.946
-I don't.
-Yeah, because you didn't wanna

18:34.080 --> 18:35.715
-participate, remember?
-Because it's a waste of time.

18:35.848 --> 18:37.250
No, it is not!

18:39.352 --> 18:41.554
-[COMPUTER WHIRRING]
-[MUSIC PLAYING]

18:41.721 --> 18:44.957
-Ah, shit, no, man.
-You did that on purpose.

18:45.091 --> 18:46.759
CHICAGO: Do you
like wasting your life? Here.

18:46.893 --> 18:49.396
Watch an instructional video
you've seen a thousand times.

18:49.529 --> 18:51.898
You need
a serious attitude adjustment.

18:52.031 --> 18:54.434
I'm out. I'll see you in, like,
five minutes.

18:55.134 --> 18:58.305
Why can't you get
this stupid thing to stop?

18:58.438 --> 18:59.939
I thought you'd really,
really like it.

19:00.072 --> 19:01.841
[MUSIC PLAYING]

19:02.141 --> 19:05.978
Hello. My name is Nadine,
and I am the designer

19:06.112 --> 19:09.182
of the LSB-300
life-support bunker.

19:09.516 --> 19:10.550
If you're watching this,

19:10.983 --> 19:13.786
the lottery is over
and you are one of the lucky few

19:13.920 --> 19:16.189
who will live through
the Saharan flu epidemic.

19:16.856 --> 19:18.325
You are a survivor.

19:20.126 --> 19:21.027
If need be,

19:21.561 --> 19:24.231
your bunker can keep you alive
for up to 70 years.

19:24.364 --> 19:25.898
Yeah, I tell you,
I ain't gonna last 70 hours

19:26.032 --> 19:27.099
if this shit don't stop.

19:27.434 --> 19:29.035
BOSTON: It'll work itself out.
Just calm down.

19:29.168 --> 19:30.303
Oh, you want to trade bunkers?

19:30.470 --> 19:32.639
To protect you
from surface conditions,

19:32.939 --> 19:35.608
your bunker
is 30 feet underground.

19:35.775 --> 19:37.277
The artificial day cycle

19:37.410 --> 19:39.646
will keep
your sleep patterns normal.

19:39.912 --> 19:41.147
Your bunker is stocked

19:41.381 --> 19:44.284
with enough Supplival powder
to last a lifetime.

19:46.185 --> 19:48.521
When mixed with water,
Supplival creates

19:48.655 --> 19:51.458
a delicious shake
that's packed with nutrients

19:51.624 --> 19:54.026
in vanilla, strawberry
or chocolate.

19:54.160 --> 19:56.028
This is so not
a chocolate shake.

19:56.463 --> 19:57.464
The generator powers

19:57.897 --> 19:59.932
the bunker's closed-loop air
and water filtration.

20:00.066 --> 20:02.502
One hundred percent
of what you consume is recycled.

20:02.635 --> 20:04.371
Wait a minute. Does that mean
we drink our own piss?

20:04.504 --> 20:06.038
DENVER:
You just now realized that?

20:06.172 --> 20:07.307
Science is amazing.

20:07.840 --> 20:09.208
NADINE: The Generator
also powers

20:09.342 --> 20:10.777
the atmosphere purifier.

20:11.043 --> 20:13.546
The purifier filters
contaminated air molecules

20:13.680 --> 20:15.214
and strips them off the virus.

20:15.348 --> 20:18.217
The 500,000 bunkers
that make up the network,

20:18.351 --> 20:21.754
operate in tandem
to eliminate the viral threat.

20:21.888 --> 20:23.690
The network generates
an estimate

20:23.823 --> 20:27.026
for how long this process
will take based on daily data,

20:27.327 --> 20:29.529
which you can view
on your statistics terminal.

20:29.796 --> 20:31.998
Solitary habitation is necessary

20:32.131 --> 20:34.734
to ensure that the virus
spreads no further.

20:35.234 --> 20:37.770
To combat the inevitable sense
of isolation,

20:38.538 --> 20:40.840
we created Domain.

20:41.708 --> 20:43.276
Domain is an information

20:43.410 --> 20:45.878
and social networking platform.

20:46.646 --> 20:51.217
Domain also allows full access
to our encyclopedia archives.

20:51.818 --> 20:53.953
Studies found that groups
of seven

20:54.153 --> 20:57.924
create an ideal long-term
social-networking community.

20:58.325 --> 21:00.159
Each group of seven was selected

21:00.293 --> 21:04.130
using algorithms derived
from your personal histories.

21:04.764 --> 21:07.567
Right now, I, too,
am probably living out my days

21:07.700 --> 21:10.570
in an LSB-300 just like yours,

21:11.237 --> 21:13.340
wondering how much longer
I'll be down here.

21:14.206 --> 21:15.342
One thing is certain:

21:15.875 --> 21:18.110
we will eradicate
the Saharan flu.

21:18.745 --> 21:21.448
Your efforts matter. You matter.

21:22.281 --> 21:23.783
We are the survivors.

21:24.484 --> 21:26.653
An Earth free
of this virus awaits.

21:27.219 --> 21:29.956
Humanity is counting on us.

21:49.909 --> 21:50.977
What is it?

21:53.212 --> 21:54.246
I was just thinking,

21:54.614 --> 21:56.182
when we finally get out
of here...

21:57.049 --> 21:59.352
are we gonna call each other
by our real names?

22:00.987 --> 22:03.022
Dean Atkins.

22:04.857 --> 22:06.959
It sounds so strange
coming out of your mouth.

22:10.096 --> 22:11.163
Say mine.

22:12.131 --> 22:13.700
Kimberly Miller.

22:14.634 --> 22:15.802
[CHUCKLES]

22:16.703 --> 22:18.371
[GROANS]
That sounds so weird.

22:18.505 --> 22:19.472
[CHUCKLES]

22:19.972 --> 22:21.674
Let's just stick
with our handles.

22:22.542 --> 22:23.543
[ALARM BEEPING]

22:23.776 --> 22:25.878
AUTOMATED FEMALE VOICE:
Warning. Warning.

22:26.312 --> 22:28.848
Warning. Power backup
below 50 percent.

22:28.981 --> 22:30.717
Charge generator immediately.

22:30.850 --> 22:32.218
Atlanta,
you gotta make this a routine.

22:32.351 --> 22:34.554
-You can't skip any more days.
-ATLANTA: I know. I know.

22:34.821 --> 22:37.356
Its's not like I have to watch
my figure for anybody down here.

22:37.590 --> 22:40.126
AUTOMATED FEMALE VOICE: Warning.
Power backup below 50 percent.

22:40.292 --> 22:42.361
Charge generator immediately.

22:44.196 --> 22:46.232
[ELECTRICITY SPARKING]

22:51.438 --> 22:53.706
-Do you guys see this?
-What is it?

22:54.373 --> 22:55.875
My terminal's freaking out.

22:57.844 --> 22:59.812
Oh, that is weird. Mine, too.

22:59.946 --> 23:02.248
[POWER WHIRRING]

23:02.515 --> 23:04.784
Well, now it's--
Now it's totally dead.

23:05.518 --> 23:08.087
-What the fuck?
-This a glitch?

23:09.255 --> 23:10.457
Maybe it's just rebooting.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.224
No, mine's--
Mine's completely off.

23:12.425 --> 23:13.560
DENVER: This is not good.

23:13.760 --> 23:15.795
These are supposed to be
on all the time.

23:15.928 --> 23:17.730
That's-- That's the whole point,
live data.

23:18.230 --> 23:19.466
Fuck is going on?

23:20.032 --> 23:21.901
I mean, first my sleep cycle?
Now this bullshit?

23:22.034 --> 23:23.903
This is affecting all of us.
You know, your sleep cycle,

23:24.036 --> 23:25.204
that's probably just
a malfunction.

23:25.337 --> 23:26.973
How the hell do you know that?
How do you know

23:27.106 --> 23:28.475
someone's not just fucking
with me on purpose?

23:28.608 --> 23:29.942
-Who would do that?
-HOUSTON: How about Orlando?

23:30.076 --> 23:31.143
He fucking hates us for sure.

23:31.277 --> 23:33.913
That's it, guys. The end of days
are upon us.

23:34.046 --> 23:35.715
Could really do
without your sarcasm right now.

23:35.848 --> 23:37.850
-I'm not being sarcastic.
-You know, I don't know, guys.

23:37.984 --> 23:39.085
This is making me kind of worry.

23:39.586 --> 23:41.220
BOSTON: Relax. It'll probably
come back on in a minute.

23:41.353 --> 23:42.955
Probably? What do you mean,
"Probably"?

23:43.189 --> 23:44.557
We have no idea
if it'll come back on.

23:44.824 --> 23:46.225
-I'm an optimistic guy.
-DENVER: We are spread out

23:46.358 --> 23:47.894
over the entire country.

23:48.094 --> 23:50.863
You understand there's no--
There's no actual physical wires

23:50.997 --> 23:52.231
connecting our bunkers.

23:52.765 --> 23:54.366
This has to be
a systemic shutdown.

23:54.501 --> 23:55.535
It's pure speculation.

23:55.668 --> 23:58.037
You know,
for a self-appointed leader,

23:58.437 --> 24:01.240
you are depressingly short
on actual ideas.

24:01.373 --> 24:02.709
Okay, well,
what brilliant suggestions

24:02.842 --> 24:04.276
-do you have then, Denver?
-DENVER: I'm not saying

24:04.410 --> 24:06.579
I have one. I just don't think
sticking your head in the sand

24:06.713 --> 24:07.780
should be an option.

24:09.816 --> 24:11.584
I think we should turn
Orlando's feedback on.

24:11.718 --> 24:12.919
-What? No-- No!
-Why?

24:13.052 --> 24:15.154
Maybe we broke the system
when we banned him.

24:16.556 --> 24:17.624
Think about it.
There are supposed

24:17.924 --> 24:20.760
to be seven of us and right now,
there are only six.

24:21.127 --> 24:23.530
-Maybe we caused the glitch.
-[SCOFFS] That is pretty thin.

24:23.663 --> 24:26.265
We banned him.
We don't want him here!

24:26.398 --> 24:28.535
Listen, Atlanta, I know.
I don't like him either...

24:29.502 --> 24:31.203
but without the terminal,

24:31.337 --> 24:33.506
we're blind to everything
that's going on outside.

24:34.406 --> 24:36.108
Bringing Orlando back
might fix the problem.

24:36.242 --> 24:39.111
-No, we voted on this.
-Yeah, like, eight months ago.

24:39.979 --> 24:41.781
The ban, it was--
It was permanent.

24:41.914 --> 24:44.517
Denver...
you out of all people

24:44.651 --> 24:46.118
have gotta be able to figure
that out.

24:46.452 --> 24:49.288
No, I-- I really don't think
that's possible.

24:49.756 --> 24:50.590
Really?

24:51.223 --> 24:52.491
Seriously,
you're not even gonna try.

24:52.625 --> 24:53.526
Yeah, okay...

24:54.160 --> 24:56.362
I'll try but I'm telling you,
everything I know

24:56.596 --> 24:58.097
says that this isn't gonna work.

24:58.798 --> 25:00.166
Well, there you go.
It's a nonissue.

25:01.333 --> 25:02.201
Fine.

25:06.105 --> 25:07.607
Phoenix, what are you doing?

25:12.344 --> 25:14.480
Stop. You--
You already did that today.

25:15.648 --> 25:16.583
Phoenix.

25:17.984 --> 25:21.588
Listen, it doesn't store
extra energy or...

25:27.159 --> 25:28.160
Phoenix.

25:29.662 --> 25:32.431
-Phoenix, why are you mad?
-Because you won't even try.

25:34.333 --> 25:36.402
-I sa-- I will try.
-But it won't work.

25:36.535 --> 25:37.870
And so if you don't think
it's gonna work,

25:38.004 --> 25:39.338
then you're not gonna
make it work.

25:41.774 --> 25:42.909
Will you s...

25:44.010 --> 25:46.312
Phoenix, will you stop, please?

25:46.979 --> 25:49.716
Please, just sit down
and talk to me.

26:10.302 --> 26:12.471
I want to help, okay?

26:14.206 --> 26:15.207
Do you?

26:16.508 --> 26:18.811
Yes. Why would you say that?
Of course I do.

26:19.912 --> 26:21.580
Then let me do this
at my own pace.

26:24.016 --> 26:25.251
Okay. I'm not...

26:26.018 --> 26:28.721
trying to force anything.
I-- I just wanna help.

26:33.893 --> 26:36.095
[SIGHS] I don't know
where to start.

26:40.299 --> 26:42.301
This is about your mom, right?

26:47.339 --> 26:48.741
My mom isn't alive.

26:50.576 --> 26:51.711
Yeah, I know.

26:53.245 --> 26:55.147
I mean, she wasn't alive
before all this.

27:02.421 --> 27:03.389
I...

27:05.858 --> 27:07.593
I was in prison
when I won the lottery.

27:10.229 --> 27:11.230
Really?

27:14.233 --> 27:15.267
What happened?

27:17.069 --> 27:19.638
I never knew my dad,
'cause he died when I was young.

27:22.675 --> 27:24.010
My mom raised me alone.

27:25.912 --> 27:27.714
She worked constantly,
'cause she had to.

27:30.449 --> 27:32.484
I spent a lot
of my teenage years alone...

27:33.920 --> 27:35.321
got in with a bad crowd...

27:36.655 --> 27:39.358
got into drugs, mostly meth.

27:41.761 --> 27:43.730
I lied, stole...

27:45.832 --> 27:47.633
ran away from home
when I was 17...

27:49.501 --> 27:50.970
came back when I OD'ed.

27:53.572 --> 27:54.540
Didn't stop.

27:58.310 --> 27:59.445
Uh, one night...

28:00.512 --> 28:02.281
[CLEARS THROAT] I got high...

28:03.315 --> 28:04.283
paranoid...

28:05.584 --> 28:07.453
accused my mom
of stealing my stash.

28:18.998 --> 28:19.999
Um...

28:21.367 --> 28:22.869
[PHOENIX CRIES]

28:24.236 --> 28:25.604
I went down to the kitchen...

28:27.639 --> 28:29.075
grabbed a paring knife...

28:30.676 --> 28:33.345
went back up the stairs
and I-- I stabbed her.

28:45.691 --> 28:47.994
Uh, the drugs were
in my room where I left 'em.

28:54.333 --> 28:55.868
I'm so sorry, Phoenix.

28:57.837 --> 28:59.538
I wish I could hold you
right now.

29:02.041 --> 29:03.342
[SIGHS]

29:05.377 --> 29:06.545
When did this happen?

29:09.816 --> 29:11.283
I was in prison a year
when the flu hit,

29:11.417 --> 29:13.085
so almost seven years ago now.

29:17.489 --> 29:20.259
The whole Orlando thing
makes a lot of sense now.

29:21.861 --> 29:23.062
Banning him was wrong.

29:26.265 --> 29:27.566
Who am I to judge?

29:28.734 --> 29:30.937
Phoenix, it's not the same.

29:33.139 --> 29:34.640
Yeah, you're right.
What I did was worse.

29:34.907 --> 29:36.075
-Phoenix--
-I'm not looking

29:36.208 --> 29:37.243
for your sympathy.

29:39.545 --> 29:41.780
Lifting the ban on Orlando
is the right thing to do.

29:44.650 --> 29:45.517
Okay.

29:47.053 --> 29:48.020
Okay, you're right.

29:48.921 --> 29:51.457
I will do everything I can
to lift the ban.

30:02.434 --> 30:03.903
I'm lucky to have you here
with me.

30:06.105 --> 30:07.273
I'm the lucky one.

30:11.377 --> 30:12.311
[SHOWER RUNNING]

31:30.756 --> 31:32.591
-DENVER: Phoenix!
-Mm.

31:35.161 --> 31:36.628
-Mm, what's going on?
-Phoenix, hey.

31:36.762 --> 31:38.965
I-- I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to scare you.

31:39.231 --> 31:40.967
-Um...
-What time is it?

31:41.233 --> 31:42.401
DENVER:
It's-- It's early-- Late.

31:42.568 --> 31:43.835
It's late, maybe. I don't know.

31:44.136 --> 31:45.537
I don't know. I've been working
on lifting this ban thing,

31:45.671 --> 31:46.973
but I think I--
I figured it out.

31:47.106 --> 31:48.740
[KEYPAD TYPING]

31:52.911 --> 31:55.614
-Did you have any luck?
-I'm not 100 percent sure

31:55.747 --> 31:56.949
that this is gonna work, but...

31:58.250 --> 32:00.252
there is a possibility
that I-- I could ban myself

32:00.386 --> 32:02.554
-or one of you guys.
-Okay, well, don't do that.

32:02.688 --> 32:04.590
I know. I--
I don't want to do that,

32:04.723 --> 32:06.558
but are you sure
that we shouldn't tell

32:06.725 --> 32:07.626
the others about this?

32:07.893 --> 32:09.528
Why? So Boston
can tell us not to do it?

32:09.661 --> 32:11.030
-I mean, what's the point?
-Yeah.

32:11.563 --> 32:13.365
Okay. You're right.
You're right. Um...

32:13.499 --> 32:14.700
[KEYPAD TYPING]

32:16.435 --> 32:17.703
Here we go.

32:26.045 --> 32:27.313
Orlando.

32:31.150 --> 32:32.418
Orlando, are you there?

32:34.253 --> 32:36.122
Orlando, it's--
It's Phoenix and Denver.

32:36.255 --> 32:37.489
We turned your feed back on.

32:42.328 --> 32:43.362
Can you hear us?

32:46.598 --> 32:49.001
[KEYPAD TYPING]

32:49.968 --> 32:52.138
-What are you doing?
-I'm checking the logs

32:52.271 --> 32:53.772
-for information.
-[KEYPAD TYPING CONTINUES]

32:58.110 --> 32:59.145
Come on. Say something.

33:02.948 --> 33:04.316
There's-- There's nothing here.

33:08.554 --> 33:09.588
What are you doing?

33:09.955 --> 33:11.423
PHOENIX: I don't know.
I'm just looking to see

33:11.557 --> 33:12.591
if I can find something.

33:14.893 --> 33:15.861
There's gotta be something.

33:16.995 --> 33:18.697
-Where is he?
-Maybe he...

33:19.331 --> 33:21.667
-escaped?
-Maybe he's dead.

33:22.801 --> 33:23.869
We have to tell the others.

33:24.736 --> 33:26.438
I'm really disappointed
in both of you.

33:26.672 --> 33:27.906
I thought
that you'd show more respect

33:28.040 --> 33:29.475
for our system,
which we all agreed on,

33:29.608 --> 33:30.676
-by the way.
-We just felt this

33:30.909 --> 33:32.010
was important enough
to make our own decision.

33:32.144 --> 33:33.579
That's not how we do things!

33:33.712 --> 33:36.148
We put you in charge
six years ago.

33:36.282 --> 33:37.849
Maybe it's time we change
some of these old rules.

33:37.983 --> 33:39.918
Oh, I see how you wanna play it.
You wanna be in charge?

33:40.052 --> 33:41.687
Why does anybody have
to be in charge?

33:41.820 --> 33:43.322
I think it's important
that we have a leader.

33:43.489 --> 33:44.756
I mean, personally,
I find it comforting.

33:44.890 --> 33:46.192
You can't figure out what's up
on your own?

33:46.325 --> 33:47.259
Why are you antagonizing me?

33:47.393 --> 33:48.560
-I'm just asking a question.
-No.

33:48.894 --> 33:51.397
-Now you're being disingenuous.
-From where I'm sitting, Boston,

33:51.530 --> 33:54.032
he-- He's not in charge
of fucking jack shit, man.

33:54.166 --> 33:57.103
Look, I am really sorry
about your sleep cycle.

33:57.236 --> 33:58.870
I wish there was something
I could do about it.

33:59.004 --> 34:01.740
Stop fucking changing!
You're fucking-- I can't!

34:01.873 --> 34:03.041
-[POWER CRACKLING]
-Stop fucking changing,

34:03.175 --> 34:04.676
you broken piece
of fucking shit!

34:04.810 --> 34:06.478
Houston, calm down.
You're not helping.

34:06.612 --> 34:07.813
I don't give a shit.
I've been awake

34:07.979 --> 34:10.014
for three fucking days.
I'm losing my fucking mind.

34:12.184 --> 34:13.851
This is fucking Orlando.
That's what it is.

34:13.985 --> 34:14.886
What?
What are you talking about?

34:15.387 --> 34:18.257
He's fucking mad at me,
'cause I fucking voted him out

34:18.389 --> 34:19.491
and now he's fucking with me.

34:19.690 --> 34:21.360
Houston, Houston,
you didn't vote against him.

34:21.493 --> 34:22.561
You didn't vote at all.
Remember?

34:22.694 --> 34:23.929
He voted himself out.

34:24.062 --> 34:26.063
Whoever built this shit,
he's fucking tough, bro.

34:26.632 --> 34:27.866
And he's fucking--

34:28.065 --> 34:29.735
He's doing this shit to me
on purpose...

34:30.835 --> 34:32.138
'cause he fucking hates me.

34:33.705 --> 34:34.973
I mean,
why else is my sleep cycle

34:35.107 --> 34:36.074
fucking doing this shit?

34:36.574 --> 34:38.543
There's a hundred reasons
it could be broken, Houston.

34:38.710 --> 34:40.712
ATLANTA: Please, sit down.

34:41.746 --> 34:43.149
I don't like seeing you
like this.

34:47.786 --> 34:49.655
Is there any chance

34:49.888 --> 34:52.824
that Orlando can actually be
in there somewhere?

34:53.458 --> 34:56.594
I mean, there's a possibility
he could be dead or...

34:58.029 --> 34:59.298
I don't know,
hiding from the camera,

34:59.431 --> 35:01.400
but that doesn't seem
like his personality.

35:02.734 --> 35:04.136
Well, what if he tried
to escape?

35:04.903 --> 35:07.639
How could he escape?
The doors are locked.

35:12.744 --> 35:15.147
Has anyone tried their door
since the terminal shut down?

35:27.726 --> 35:28.960
What if it actually opens?

35:29.528 --> 35:31.263
You could be exposed.

35:37.836 --> 35:40.372
Phoenix! Don't.

35:43.909 --> 35:45.377
Phoenix, wait-- Wait-- Wait!
No, no, no! What are--

35:45.511 --> 35:46.845
Think about it!
Think about what you're doing.

35:47.145 --> 35:48.046
Stop!

36:29.655 --> 36:31.557
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

37:15.634 --> 37:16.535
Hey.

37:18.236 --> 37:19.104
Hi.

37:20.506 --> 37:23.509
I'm trying to be zen
about what you and Denver did.

37:24.042 --> 37:26.678
We agreed on a hierarchy
way back when all this started,

37:26.878 --> 37:28.747
but all of a sudden,
you and Denver,

37:28.880 --> 37:30.849
you guys decided
to do your own thing.

37:31.049 --> 37:32.784
Well, we've been in here
for years.

37:33.852 --> 37:35.421
Things can't stay
the same forever.

37:35.554 --> 37:37.289
But that doesn't mean
you should do whatever you want,

37:37.423 --> 37:38.590
-whenever you want.
-You know that lifting

37:38.724 --> 37:40.326
the ban on Orlando
was the smart thing to do.

37:40.459 --> 37:43.395
You sound more and more like him
as the years roll on.

37:43.529 --> 37:44.730
-Like who?
-Denver.

37:45.531 --> 37:46.665
I mean, you're two peas
in a pod.

37:46.798 --> 37:48.066
Well, it's no secret
we're together.

37:48.199 --> 37:49.134
"Together."

37:49.935 --> 37:51.437
I mean, what does
that even mean down here?

37:51.570 --> 37:53.805
It means we see a future
with one another.

37:54.039 --> 37:56.274
I will never understand,
why him?

37:57.609 --> 38:00.245
-As opposed to you?
-No, I me-- I mean, that's--

38:00.479 --> 38:02.280
-that's not what I mean.
-I'm sorry to be blunt,

38:02.414 --> 38:04.249
but it's absolutely none
of your business.

38:04.383 --> 38:06.685
Look, I'm just worried
about you, okay?

38:07.919 --> 38:08.987
I mean, there's something
about him

38:09.220 --> 38:10.722
that gives me the creeps.
Don't you see that?

38:10.856 --> 38:11.923
No, I don't.

38:12.458 --> 38:14.493
He's never been anything
but supportive and loving.

38:14.626 --> 38:15.827
You never even met him
in person.

38:16.127 --> 38:18.597
I never met you in person
and you expect me to trust you.

38:19.631 --> 38:21.132
What is this about, Boston?

38:21.633 --> 38:23.234
Denver reminds me
of my dad,

38:24.035 --> 38:26.505
his looks, his voice,
his mannerisms, everything.

38:27.339 --> 38:28.374
You know, on the surface,

38:28.740 --> 38:30.809
he's really friendly,
super smart, and charming,

38:30.976 --> 38:32.578
but there was something
really fake about it all.

38:33.579 --> 38:35.814
I mean, he was mean as shit
behind closed doors.

38:35.947 --> 38:39.250
You hit this switch
and, snap, he was a monster.

38:40.018 --> 38:42.220
Listen, I always appreciate
your honesty,

38:42.854 --> 38:44.423
and thank you for your concern,

38:44.923 --> 38:46.825
but I know Denver,

38:47.459 --> 38:48.960
and he is nothing like...

38:49.761 --> 38:50.862
your father.

38:52.163 --> 38:53.131
Okay.

39:46.685 --> 39:47.653
[SIGHS]

39:48.119 --> 39:49.154
PHOENIX: What are you thinking
about right now?

39:49.755 --> 39:51.089
[SIGHS] You.

39:52.424 --> 39:55.360
PHOENIX: I know, but what,
specifically?

39:56.762 --> 39:58.063
[SIGHS]

39:59.330 --> 40:00.532
What it would feel like...

40:01.800 --> 40:03.602
to have my hands all
over your body.

40:06.572 --> 40:07.606
PHOENIX: What else?

40:07.773 --> 40:09.808
What your lips would taste like.

40:11.042 --> 40:11.943
PHOENIX: And?

40:16.648 --> 40:17.649
What your...

40:18.817 --> 40:20.719
What you would feel like
underneath me.

40:24.856 --> 40:26.592
Taste of your sweat. Mm.

40:36.502 --> 40:37.869
PHOENIX:
How hard are you fucking me?

40:38.436 --> 40:40.205
Oh, I'm fucking you so hard.

40:41.740 --> 40:43.875
[SIGHS] I'm thinking
about you looking back at me.

40:44.142 --> 40:45.343
PHOENIX: You gonna come?

40:46.578 --> 40:47.513
I want you to come.

40:48.246 --> 40:50.949
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

40:58.590 --> 40:59.658
[LAUGHS]

40:59.958 --> 41:00.992
PHOENIX: How was that?

41:01.459 --> 41:03.328
[SIGHS]
Oh, man.

41:04.496 --> 41:07.499
Oh, I hope nobody plays
that back. [LAUGHS]

41:08.734 --> 41:11.803
PHOENIX: [LAUGHING]
Who cares if they do?

41:12.771 --> 41:14.205
[EXHALES]

41:16.207 --> 41:17.743
I love you so much.

41:35.126 --> 41:36.427
PHOENIX: Denver.

41:37.929 --> 41:38.864
Hi.

41:39.330 --> 41:40.198
Hi.

41:42.300 --> 41:43.368
Mm.

41:46.772 --> 41:47.806
PHOENIX: Are you reading?

41:47.939 --> 41:50.041
No. No, I was just--
I was at the pool,

41:50.175 --> 41:51.977
-thought I'd do a couple laps.
-PHOENIX: Nice.

41:56.481 --> 41:59.350
Oh, let me guess.
You're reading, uh, No Exit.

42:00.952 --> 42:02.020
How many times
have you read that?

42:02.153 --> 42:03.589
I don't know. I lost count.

42:03.722 --> 42:06.157
-Wow. It's that good, huh?
-Yeah. I like it.

42:06.291 --> 42:07.993
You know, it's a--
It's a classic.

42:09.895 --> 42:10.862
What's up?

42:10.996 --> 42:12.197
Do you remember
when we used to record

42:12.330 --> 42:13.932
those private videos?

42:14.666 --> 42:15.834
I do, yeah.

42:16.234 --> 42:19.638
What if Orlando made some
of his own while he was banned?

42:20.939 --> 42:22.407
Do you think
you could access them?

42:23.508 --> 42:25.877
Yeah. I mean,
if they're not hidden very well.

42:26.044 --> 42:26.978
Um...

42:29.014 --> 42:32.083
While I'm doing this,
what made you...

42:33.051 --> 42:34.485
wanna watch those videos?

42:36.187 --> 42:37.589
Just wanted to think
about something nice.

42:38.056 --> 42:40.726
So a video of me getting off,
that-- That did the trick?

42:41.059 --> 42:41.960
Oh, totally.

42:42.160 --> 42:44.930
Okay. I got some, uh,
right here.

42:45.697 --> 42:48.266
Oh, I got a bunch. Okay, I--
I'll screen-share it with you.

42:49.267 --> 42:51.903
This one's
from a couple months ago.

42:53.438 --> 42:54.305
Play it.

42:56.174 --> 42:58.076
[ORLANDO GRUNTING]

43:02.213 --> 43:05.250
Day 121. I feel amazing.

43:05.751 --> 43:08.053
I don't think I've ever been
in better shape. [YELLS]

43:08.186 --> 43:09.220
-He seems fine.
-[ORLANDO YELLING]

43:09.354 --> 43:10.421
Guess he wasn't lying
when he said

43:10.555 --> 43:11.723
he wouldn't miss us.

43:13.792 --> 43:16.327
-Well, that was uneventful.
-Play a different one.

43:17.763 --> 43:18.797
Okay.

43:22.000 --> 43:23.101
[ORLANDO EXHALES]

43:24.202 --> 43:27.706
I did not realize he was such
a workout enthusiast.

43:30.575 --> 43:31.910
Day 186.

43:32.410 --> 43:33.779
Guess what.
I'm gonna be a frigging Hulk

43:33.912 --> 43:35.313
when I get out of here, huh?
[CLAPS]

43:35.446 --> 43:38.216
Huh?
[LAUGHS]

43:41.887 --> 43:43.621
Oh, I guess...

43:44.756 --> 43:46.157
There's--
There's hundreds of these.

43:46.357 --> 43:48.794
Yeah, it's like Orlando's video
workout series.

43:49.060 --> 43:50.395
Okay, here's the last one.

43:50.729 --> 43:53.865
It's from a few days ago.
It's a much bigger file.

43:55.100 --> 43:57.703
[CONTROLLED BREATHING]

43:59.270 --> 44:00.638
[STATIC CRACKLING]

44:01.840 --> 44:02.941
What is this?

44:04.109 --> 44:06.978
-I don't know.
-[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

44:10.148 --> 44:12.383
ORLANDO: Leave me alone!
Leave me alone!

44:12.617 --> 44:13.685
[THUDDING]

44:17.455 --> 44:18.724
Wait. What just happened?

44:19.590 --> 44:21.226
I don't understand.
He-- He's gone.

44:23.428 --> 44:24.830
-PHOENIX: Oh, my God.
-DENVER: What?

44:25.563 --> 44:27.999
Look at his door.
His door is open.

44:29.567 --> 44:30.836
What do you mean it's--
That's not--

44:31.002 --> 44:32.270
That's not possible.

44:33.805 --> 44:35.340
Wait. Go back to the static.

44:36.808 --> 44:38.676
[STATIC CRACKLING]

44:39.745 --> 44:41.679
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

44:41.980 --> 44:42.981
There. Did you hear that?

44:43.114 --> 44:44.315
-ORLANDO: What?
-Yeah. What is that?

44:44.649 --> 44:47.052
-Sounds like screaming.
-Is that Orlando?

44:48.119 --> 44:50.188
-How long is this video?
-It's long.

44:50.588 --> 44:52.023
There's five hours of this.

44:52.457 --> 44:54.225
-Go to the very end.
-Hang on.

45:12.643 --> 45:14.079
HOUSTON: See, what I think
is that Orlando set

45:14.212 --> 45:15.546
this whole thing up, all right?
He's the one--

45:15.680 --> 45:17.015
He's the one who put us in here.

45:17.182 --> 45:19.217
He tricked us into thinking
that the Saharan flu is real

45:19.350 --> 45:21.019
and then he made us
wait down here for five years.

45:21.152 --> 45:22.720
-That's a little implausible.
-Houston,

45:22.854 --> 45:23.855
can you try to calm down?

45:24.022 --> 45:25.356
No, you guys don't see it,
but I do, okay?

45:25.490 --> 45:26.691
It makes total fucking sense
to me now,

45:26.825 --> 45:27.893
all right?
This is what he wanted.

45:28.159 --> 45:29.761
He wanted for all of us
to go fucking crazy, okay?

45:29.895 --> 45:31.696
But I fucking-- I got it,
all right? I figured it out,

45:31.830 --> 45:33.231
'cause I-- I see what he's doing
to us.

45:33.364 --> 45:34.833
BOSTON: Houston, how long
has it been since you slept?

45:34.966 --> 45:36.167
Who the fuck knows, man?
Fuck sleep.

45:36.401 --> 45:37.903
I don't need sleep. Sleep is
for weak-ass motherfuckers

45:38.036 --> 45:40.171
like you guys, okay?
But Orlando's plan,

45:40.305 --> 45:41.773
it blew up in his fucking face,
man,

45:41.907 --> 45:44.175
because I can see
what he fucking did to us, man.

45:44.309 --> 45:46.111
Okay, so this is
a big conspiracy theory.

45:46.244 --> 45:47.445
No, it's not a theory, man.

45:48.146 --> 45:49.347
-I know I'm right.
-You know you're right,

45:49.480 --> 45:51.549
from what, from a--
A door shutting in a video?

45:51.682 --> 45:53.251
You're just too fucking afraid
to fucking admit it, man.

45:53.384 --> 45:54.585
Will you please stop cursing?

45:54.820 --> 45:56.121
My goodness,
you're making my head spin.

45:56.254 --> 45:57.388
Maybe you need an exorcism.

45:57.522 --> 45:59.257
Sweetie, how about contributing
something useful

45:59.390 --> 46:00.391
to a stressful situation?

46:00.525 --> 46:02.293
-This video could be fake.
-How?

46:02.794 --> 46:03.895
-And why?
-That's my point.

46:04.062 --> 46:05.563
-We don't know anything.
-So, what, let me guess.

46:05.696 --> 46:07.298
Your idea is to-- To just
sit here and do nothing?

46:07.432 --> 46:09.067
-What other choice do we have?
-Well, you could be

46:09.200 --> 46:10.401
forcibly removed
like Orlando was.

46:10.535 --> 46:11.937
That is pure speculation.

46:12.070 --> 46:14.072
How many times
can you say the same thing?

46:14.205 --> 46:16.341
As many times as I have to
to get you to listen to reason.

46:16.474 --> 46:17.442
Maybe the terminal shut down,

46:17.575 --> 46:18.844
because we don't
need it anymore.

46:19.144 --> 46:20.946
-Maybe the flu is gone.
-Yeah, Atlanta,

46:21.212 --> 46:22.981
maybe we'll all be saved.

46:23.114 --> 46:24.782
Maybe in a few days,
we'll just walk out of here

46:24.916 --> 46:25.851
and everything'll be perfect.

46:25.984 --> 46:27.085
You know,
maybe your little angels

46:27.285 --> 46:29.154
-are alive and all grown up.
-Are you done yet?

46:29.554 --> 46:31.389
Are you done
with your little tantrum?

46:32.123 --> 46:34.225
We need to take action
while we still have control.

46:34.359 --> 46:36.227
Hey, Phoenix, man,
I hate to break it to you,

46:36.361 --> 46:37.896
but we ain't in control of shit,
all right?

46:38.029 --> 46:40.765
Orlando, Orlando's running
this whole fucking game, man.

46:40.899 --> 46:42.567
-He got us beat.
-I hope you're right, Houston.

46:43.534 --> 46:44.602
I really do.

46:45.236 --> 46:46.671
Because that's better
than the alternative.

46:46.804 --> 46:48.006
Well, do you have a plan,
Phoenix?

46:48.139 --> 46:49.674
Yeah. I think we should find
a way out.

46:49.807 --> 46:50.942
You all sound crazy to me.

46:51.142 --> 46:52.777
Maybe the lock that seals
the door can be broken.

46:52.911 --> 46:54.779
Sudden depressurization
could be fatal.

46:54.913 --> 46:56.747
Well, that's a risk
that I'm willing to take.

46:56.882 --> 46:58.850
-BOSTON: In here, we're safe.
-We're not safe

46:58.984 --> 47:00.651
-and that video is proof.
-BOSTON: It doesn't prove

47:00.785 --> 47:02.120
anything. I'm still
not convinced it's real.

47:02.253 --> 47:03.654
What else do you need?

47:04.589 --> 47:05.991
We don't know what's going on.

47:06.124 --> 47:08.293
-We have to do something.
-Okay. Let's vote.

47:08.426 --> 47:10.195
I don't need your permission
to make my own plan.

47:10.328 --> 47:12.363
-Can I have two votes?
-Houston, concentrate.

47:12.663 --> 47:15.033
Stop, officer. Don't shoot me.

47:15.967 --> 47:17.502
[CHUCKLES] I used to say
that shit all the time

47:17.635 --> 47:19.204
when I was a kid.
Hey, you guys ever have

47:19.337 --> 47:20.805
-the cops put a gun on you?
-BOSTON: Houston!

47:20.939 --> 47:22.240
Fuck, man! Fuck, yeah! We escape

47:22.373 --> 47:23.975
and go find that
lying motherfucker, Orlando!

47:24.109 --> 47:25.877
We skin him alive! Sounds like
a fuckin' plan to me!

47:26.011 --> 47:27.478
-BOSTON: He's lost his mind.
-I lost my mind,

47:27.645 --> 47:30.048
then I found it.
It's right here in my head.

47:30.916 --> 47:32.951
ATLANTA: Listen, we can't make
any decisions

47:33.084 --> 47:34.385
with Houston like this.

47:42.493 --> 47:44.829
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

48:08.987 --> 48:10.355
[WHIRRING]

48:27.038 --> 48:27.973
DENVER: Good evening.

48:30.408 --> 48:31.276
PHOENIX: Hi.

48:32.143 --> 48:33.211
What are you doing up?

48:34.712 --> 48:36.447
DENVER:
You know, just checking in.

48:37.682 --> 48:39.450
-Can you even see anything?
-PHOENIX: Sort of.

48:39.884 --> 48:42.353
Figured I'd do Boston the favor
of not searching...

48:42.920 --> 48:45.590
-directly in front of his face.
-DENVER: That's very sweet.

48:46.224 --> 48:47.292
Did you find anything yet?

48:48.226 --> 48:49.894
Nope, not really.

48:53.164 --> 48:55.466
DENVER: Uh, you know,
it is the middle of the night,

48:55.700 --> 48:57.735
so maybe you should try
and get some sleep.

48:58.103 --> 48:59.037
Yeah.

48:59.604 --> 49:00.705
I can't really sleep.

49:01.606 --> 49:02.707
What's up?

49:03.941 --> 49:05.276
I was trying to remember...

49:06.244 --> 49:09.280
what everyone's real name is.

49:10.148 --> 49:11.482
There's, uh, Barry.

49:12.483 --> 49:14.152
-Raymond.
-Olivia.

49:14.752 --> 49:16.487
-Cedric.
-And then...

49:18.456 --> 49:19.757
-Houston.
-[DISTANT THUD]

49:19.957 --> 49:21.926
-What's his real name?
-Huh.

49:22.327 --> 49:23.928
-[THUDDING CONTINUES]
-I don't think he ever told us.

49:25.630 --> 49:26.697
-[THUDDING]
-Do you hear that?

49:27.432 --> 49:28.433
Yeah, what is that?

49:31.802 --> 49:33.004
[THUDDING]

49:36.474 --> 49:37.442
Houston.

49:38.243 --> 49:39.577
Oh, no.

49:48.586 --> 49:49.820
-Houston.
-[THUDDING CONTINUES]

49:49.954 --> 49:51.689
What is going on?

49:52.590 --> 49:53.624
Oh, shit.

49:59.397 --> 50:00.865
Houston, stop.

50:01.766 --> 50:02.767
[POWER CRACKLING]

50:03.234 --> 50:05.670
[LAUGHS]

50:26.491 --> 50:28.393
[LAUGHS]

50:31.962 --> 50:32.830
Houston.

50:34.399 --> 50:36.701
[LAUGHS]

50:44.442 --> 50:46.844
[LAUGHS]

50:57.322 --> 50:59.224
[SCREAMS]

51:21.679 --> 51:22.780
[THUDDING]

51:35.693 --> 51:36.794
What the...

51:46.704 --> 51:48.539
You still think we're safe
in here, Boston?

52:05.856 --> 52:06.891
I'm scared.

52:09.560 --> 52:10.595
Me, too.

52:14.064 --> 52:15.466
-Who are they?
-[DENVER SIGHS]

52:16.133 --> 52:17.468
I don't know. I don't...

52:19.136 --> 52:21.972
People immune
to the Saharan flu? I...

52:24.409 --> 52:25.810
How are they
finding the bunkers?

52:26.644 --> 52:27.978
[SIGHS]

52:29.680 --> 52:32.283
Maybe they heard
Houston screaming.

52:36.086 --> 52:37.522
[SIGHS]

52:37.755 --> 52:39.524
I don't know. Let's just...

52:41.892 --> 52:43.594
Let's try and get some rest,
okay?

52:45.396 --> 52:46.764
-Okay.
-Good night.

52:47.064 --> 52:48.098
Good night.

52:51.836 --> 52:54.004
[PHOENIX SIGHS]

52:57.107 --> 52:58.543
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

53:37.014 --> 53:37.882
No.

53:42.820 --> 53:44.489
-BOSTON: Phoenix.
-[GASPS]

53:44.722 --> 53:46.190
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

53:47.157 --> 53:48.359
BOSTON: Don't move.

53:49.327 --> 53:51.662
-What's wrong?
-Slowly look down...

53:52.196 --> 53:54.832
but be very careful.

53:57.635 --> 53:59.870
-[RAT SQUEAKING]
-[PHOENIX EXHALES]

54:00.471 --> 54:02.172
PHOENIX: You guys scared
the hell out of me.

54:03.741 --> 54:05.343
It's just a little rat. Hi.

54:05.476 --> 54:07.345
Don't touch it.
It could be sick.

54:07.478 --> 54:09.414
No.
Only humans can get Saharan flu.

54:09.547 --> 54:12.717
-I'm talking about rabies.
-Hey there, little guy.

54:13.551 --> 54:14.552
Come here.

54:23.193 --> 54:24.462
ATLANTA: How did it get there?

54:24.762 --> 54:26.163
Aren't these things supposed
to be sealed?

54:26.297 --> 54:28.232
Oh, my God, Atlanta.
It's a miracle.

54:28.366 --> 54:30.301
No, no, Phoenix, Phoenix,
she's right.

54:30.435 --> 54:32.837
You need to be careful.
Your bunker is not airtight.

54:33.070 --> 54:34.305
I think this is my fault.

54:35.205 --> 54:37.775
I found this panel yesterday
and tried to pry it open.

54:38.242 --> 54:40.177
The rat must have knocked it out
when it came in.

54:40.645 --> 54:43.348
-What were you looking for?
-A way out.

54:46.216 --> 54:48.052
"Emergency vent."

54:56.527 --> 54:57.595
Can you see anything?

54:58.062 --> 54:59.730
No. There's nothing.

55:01.866 --> 55:03.468
Do you guys have the same panel?

55:22.353 --> 55:24.188
[SIGHS]
I don't-- I don't understand.

55:24.321 --> 55:25.956
-This doesn't make any sense.
-BOSTON: You know,

55:26.090 --> 55:27.458
maybe it's some kind
of ventilation system

55:27.625 --> 55:29.159
-that connects all the bunkers.
-DENVER: Oh, yeah.

55:29.494 --> 55:30.795
Yeah, there's ventilation ducts

55:30.928 --> 55:32.697
across
the entire continental U.S.

55:32.830 --> 55:33.998
You know what?
Stop being an asshole.

55:34.131 --> 55:35.132
I'm just brainstorming.

55:35.466 --> 55:36.967
Yeah, but aren't we
30 feet underground?

55:37.101 --> 55:38.703
Yeah, that's--
That's my point, okay?

55:38.836 --> 55:41.138
Th-- There should be dirt
on the other side of this wall,

55:41.271 --> 55:43.641
not an open space
and definitely not a vent.

55:43.774 --> 55:47.177
Does this make you guys happy...
asking all these questions?

55:47.311 --> 55:49.680
Like, do you feel like
you're making progress?

55:49.814 --> 55:51.516
Do you feel like you're solving
some mystery?

55:51.649 --> 55:53.884
So tell me, what is your idea,
hmm, Chicago?

55:54.018 --> 55:55.486
Nothing. Do nothing.

55:56.186 --> 55:57.622
Same shit's gonna happen,
regardless.

55:57.755 --> 55:59.123
For once, I agree with Chicago.

56:00.024 --> 56:01.626
-I think we should wait it out.
-DENVER: Of course,

56:01.759 --> 56:03.160
you think we should wait.
That's your answer

56:03.293 --> 56:05.229
to everything!
Sit back and wait.

56:05.430 --> 56:06.831
Well, you know what?
We've been listening to you

56:07.197 --> 56:09.867
this entire time and every day
has gotten progressively worse.

56:10.000 --> 56:12.236
So, what,
you think we could have
done something about Orlando?

56:12.537 --> 56:14.038
You think we could have done
something about Houston?

56:14.171 --> 56:15.372
About the rat? About fucking...

56:15.506 --> 56:16.707
-Stop arguing!
-BOSTON: ...any of this?

56:17.975 --> 56:19.444
What we need right now
is more information.

56:19.744 --> 56:22.212
Great idea. Just simply acquire
more information.

56:22.346 --> 56:23.681
Look, we know
that we're connected

56:23.814 --> 56:25.015
to the Domain network.

56:25.182 --> 56:27.084
There has gotta be a way
to access data

56:27.217 --> 56:28.619
-from the other bunkers.
-Even if it works,

56:28.753 --> 56:30.187
-what will it accomplish?
-I don't know, but maybe

56:30.320 --> 56:31.722
we can contact someone else.

56:31.856 --> 56:33.891
That could work. I'll--
I'll get on it.

56:34.892 --> 56:36.594
[KEYPAD TYPING]

56:36.894 --> 56:39.196
Now, I think everyone else
should start going

56:39.329 --> 56:40.798
-around the bunker--
-Who put you in charge?

56:41.231 --> 56:43.367
I'm taking charge,
because no one else is doing it.

56:43.501 --> 56:45.135
-Maybe we should vote.
-Boston, stop wasting time.

56:45.269 --> 56:46.904
-Look, I'm the one that got--
-Stop!

56:47.505 --> 56:48.539
[SIGHS]

56:49.106 --> 56:51.842
-The system is collapsing.
-The system is collapsed.

56:52.042 --> 56:54.011
Which is why we need
to find a way out of here.

56:54.178 --> 56:56.547
-[SCOFFS] How?
-I'm not sure.

56:57.181 --> 56:59.116
An emergency release?
Something.

56:59.249 --> 57:01.051
I don't know.
There's gotta be a way.

57:01.318 --> 57:03.387
Okay. Okay, okay, just,

57:03.721 --> 57:05.189
you know, tell me
where to start. I'll help.

57:05.355 --> 57:07.558
Be creative. Try-- Try anything.

57:13.030 --> 57:14.131
Boston, you, too.

57:16.266 --> 57:19.203
-Chicago, you gonna help us out?
-Sorry.

57:20.237 --> 57:22.473
-I don't do jailbreaks.
-Come on.

57:23.608 --> 57:25.810
-You're a smart guy.
-Leave me alone.

57:28.145 --> 57:29.480
What exactly are we looking
for again?

57:29.614 --> 57:30.981
Can you guys--
Can you just keep it down?

57:31.115 --> 57:32.082
I'm trying to focus.

57:32.282 --> 57:34.318
BOSTON: Oh, I'm sorry, princess.

58:31.809 --> 58:32.910
[KNOCKING]

58:43.120 --> 58:44.254
Atlanta, what are you doing?

58:44.989 --> 58:47.091
The Supplival has to be coming
from someplace.

58:47.825 --> 58:50.194
I think it's connected
to that pipe back there.

58:50.527 --> 58:51.929
I'm gonna break through.
I think there's something

58:52.062 --> 58:54.164
-on the other side.
-Atlanta, if you break that,

58:54.298 --> 58:55.700
you could cut access
to your food.

58:55.833 --> 58:57.167
PHOENIX: Yeah, I agree
with Boston.

58:57.301 --> 58:59.036
I know I told you
to try anything but--

58:59.169 --> 59:00.137
No.

59:00.938 --> 59:03.974
No, guys. Listen, if I'm gonna
end up starving to death,

59:04.308 --> 59:06.510
then I guess that was God's plan
for me all along.

59:26.330 --> 59:28.232
-What do you see?
-Nothing.

59:29.033 --> 59:31.368
It's just empty space.

59:32.870 --> 59:36.040
-You can't see anything?
-No. It's pitch-black.

59:38.208 --> 59:41.578
But there's too much space
on the other side of this wall.

59:42.747 --> 59:43.981
It doesn't make sense.

59:46.851 --> 59:48.753
[WHIRRING]

59:50.755 --> 59:51.989
Atlanta, your door.

59:56.060 --> 59:56.994
Atlanta!

01:00:07.271 --> 01:00:09.473
ATLANTA: O Lord, make me brave,

01:00:09.840 --> 01:00:11.375
brave enough to face the dark,

01:00:11.876 --> 01:00:13.443
the dark that works
to pull me in.

01:00:13.878 --> 01:00:15.379
Help me to retain my sight,

01:00:15.680 --> 01:00:17.114
to see that from the dark
comes light.

01:00:18.215 --> 01:00:21.451
Oh, no. No. Oh, God.

01:00:22.019 --> 01:00:23.988
[STATIC CRACKLING]

01:00:36.767 --> 01:00:39.036
To know that from the dark
comes light.

01:01:04.228 --> 01:01:05.295
[PIPE CLANKING]

01:01:06.663 --> 01:01:08.432
-[THUDDING]
-PHOENIX: Chicago...

01:01:09.800 --> 01:01:10.801
what are you doing?

01:01:21.445 --> 01:01:22.512
-Denver!
-What?

01:01:22.679 --> 01:01:24.715
-Atlanta's gone.
-What? When?

01:01:25.149 --> 01:01:26.483
Look at Chicago's feed.

01:01:34.158 --> 01:01:35.492
Is that Supplival?

01:01:38.628 --> 01:01:40.197
He was starving himself.

01:01:47.972 --> 01:01:50.274
Chicago, please, don't do this.

01:01:50.707 --> 01:01:52.242
We can get through this,
Chicago.

01:01:52.642 --> 01:01:53.844
Nobody's getting through.

01:01:55.012 --> 01:01:56.180
We need you.

01:01:57.381 --> 01:01:58.348
That's not true.

01:02:00.250 --> 01:02:02.386
Chicago, you don't wanna
do this. You don't.

01:02:04.889 --> 01:02:07.091
I never wanted
to do anything more.

01:02:18.402 --> 01:02:19.503
Goodbye, guys.

01:02:20.170 --> 01:02:23.673
Please, Chicago, don't do this.
No. No! No.

01:02:24.875 --> 01:02:27.845
-No.
-[CHICAGO CHOKING]

01:02:32.049 --> 01:02:33.951
[PIPE CREAKING]

01:02:53.703 --> 01:02:55.105
[CREAKING STOPS]

01:02:59.309 --> 01:03:00.444
God.

01:03:02.880 --> 01:03:04.348
I can't look at that.

01:03:06.616 --> 01:03:07.617
Then don't.

01:03:08.118 --> 01:03:10.921
Why are you so fucking cold?

01:03:12.923 --> 01:03:15.059
I'm dealing with this
in my own way, all right?

01:03:15.192 --> 01:03:18.095
Why don't you show some emotion,
you fucking robot?

01:03:18.362 --> 01:03:20.664
He was our friend.

01:03:25.369 --> 01:03:26.603
[RAT SKITTERING]

01:03:29.940 --> 01:03:30.941
PHOENIX: [WHISPERING] Hi.

01:03:32.409 --> 01:03:35.279
[SIGHS] Well, I hate to bring
this down even further,

01:03:35.412 --> 01:03:36.847
but I have some new information.

01:03:37.281 --> 01:03:38.949
New information
would be good right now.

01:03:39.516 --> 01:03:41.151
Well, that depends
on your point of view.

01:03:42.252 --> 01:03:44.188
So, the bunkers,
they're all connected, right?

01:03:44.321 --> 01:03:46.156
Every bunker in the Network
has its own feed.

01:03:46.290 --> 01:03:48.292
That's 500,000 feeds.

01:03:48.859 --> 01:03:51.328
So the Domain,
what it does is it limits access

01:03:51.628 --> 01:03:54.064
to the seven people
in your group.

01:03:54.464 --> 01:03:56.666
The feeds, they're still there
but you just can't see 'em.

01:03:57.267 --> 01:03:58.668
Well,
can you access them now?

01:03:58.936 --> 01:04:00.270
Yeah. I already did.

01:04:01.505 --> 01:04:03.840
I can only pull 'em up one
at a time. This is, uh,

01:04:04.041 --> 01:04:05.175
this is a random one.

01:04:06.010 --> 01:04:08.512
I'm-- I'm assuming
they already took this person.

01:04:10.247 --> 01:04:11.848
[INAUDIBLE]

01:04:12.016 --> 01:04:13.183
Who is that?

01:04:13.951 --> 01:04:16.053
-No idea.
-Why can't we hear him?

01:04:16.186 --> 01:04:18.222
I couldn't locate
the audio streams, video only,

01:04:18.355 --> 01:04:20.024
so we can't communicate
with them and...

01:04:21.125 --> 01:04:22.192
they can't see us.

01:04:23.928 --> 01:04:26.063
-So this is live.
-DENVER: Yeah.

01:04:28.365 --> 01:04:29.333
PHOENIX: Wow.

01:04:29.799 --> 01:04:33.037
It is so weird to see a new face
after all these years.

01:04:34.504 --> 01:04:35.472
[KEYPAD TYPING]

01:04:53.490 --> 01:04:54.558
God.

01:04:55.359 --> 01:04:56.927
I've seen a lot of suicides.

01:05:04.368 --> 01:05:07.604
This-- This-- This is just...

01:05:09.073 --> 01:05:10.907
-I don't know.
-There's more.

01:05:11.475 --> 01:05:12.376
What?

01:05:12.576 --> 01:05:14.711
[SIGHS] There's only
a thousand feeds

01:05:14.878 --> 01:05:16.213
coming from the main server.

01:05:17.214 --> 01:05:19.916
-So what?
-There should be 500,000,

01:05:20.684 --> 01:05:21.685
one from each bunker.

01:05:22.052 --> 01:05:24.554
Is it possible that you
just can't access them all?

01:05:24.688 --> 01:05:27.191
No. No. I mean,
I-- I didn't think

01:05:27.824 --> 01:05:28.925
that it was possible,

01:05:29.159 --> 01:05:31.261
so I-- I triple-checked it
but I'm telling you...

01:05:33.330 --> 01:05:34.631
there's only a thousand bunkers.

01:05:34.999 --> 01:05:38.035
-What does that mean?
-It means they lied to us.

01:05:40.870 --> 01:05:42.772
[RAT SQUEAKING]

01:05:46.876 --> 01:05:48.012
We have to get out of here.

01:05:48.645 --> 01:05:49.513
How?

01:05:52.916 --> 01:05:54.418
PHOENIX: When we were searching
the bunkers,

01:05:55.119 --> 01:05:57.521
I found this cluster
of wires connecting...

01:05:58.288 --> 01:05:59.823
the door to the computer.

01:05:59.990 --> 01:06:01.191
DENVER: So we-- If we cut it,

01:06:01.325 --> 01:06:02.592
the computer loses control
of the door?

01:06:02.959 --> 01:06:04.794
Yeah. It just might unlock it.

01:06:05.095 --> 01:06:07.797
Or we cut power to a crucial
life-support function,

01:06:07.931 --> 01:06:10.834
and we starve or suffocate
in total darkness.

01:06:11.001 --> 01:06:12.969
I have to get out of here
on my own terms.

01:06:13.737 --> 01:06:15.272
I don't wanna be pulled out
like the others.

01:06:15.539 --> 01:06:17.741
Well, let's say we do
make it out of here, all right?

01:06:17.874 --> 01:06:20.744
And we don't contract
the Saharan flu within hours.

01:06:20.877 --> 01:06:23.080
We're still thousands
of miles apart

01:06:23.380 --> 01:06:24.681
in a broken-down society.

01:06:24.948 --> 01:06:26.116
Well, we need a meeting place.

01:06:26.783 --> 01:06:28.052
We'd have to travel on foot.

01:06:28.552 --> 01:06:30.154
Maybe we can find
working vehicles.

01:06:30.920 --> 01:06:32.522
That's-- That's a huge maybe.

01:06:32.956 --> 01:06:33.957
All right.

01:06:34.758 --> 01:06:35.959
Four Corners Monument,

01:06:36.226 --> 01:06:37.794
where Arizona, Colorado,

01:06:37.961 --> 01:06:39.263
Utah and New Mexico meet.

01:06:39.629 --> 01:06:41.631
No, that's too remote.
That's not safe.

01:06:41.898 --> 01:06:43.200
That's not safe at all.

01:06:44.334 --> 01:06:46.370
-I'll come to you.
-To Phoenix?

01:06:48.305 --> 01:06:49.239
That's a whole state away.

01:06:49.473 --> 01:06:50.907
I know, but I--
I'll make it work.

01:06:51.141 --> 01:06:52.276
Is there a--
A government building,

01:06:52.409 --> 01:06:54.010
something
that's centrally located?

01:06:54.444 --> 01:06:56.480
-Yeah, City Hall.
-That's where we'll meet.

01:06:57.147 --> 01:06:59.183
-Are you sure?
-Of course.

01:07:02.119 --> 01:07:03.053
What about me?

01:07:04.621 --> 01:07:07.023
[STAMMERS]
You-- You can come, too.

01:07:07.457 --> 01:07:09.393
I'm 3,000 miles away.

01:07:14.831 --> 01:07:15.832
Never mind.

01:07:16.533 --> 01:07:18.502
Just excess baggage.
[CHUCKLES]

01:07:18.835 --> 01:07:20.204
I'll figure out
my own situation.

01:07:20.837 --> 01:07:22.038
I'm sorry, Boston.

01:07:22.972 --> 01:07:25.375
-Just one last thing, though.
-Sure.

01:07:26.810 --> 01:07:27.877
We have to vote.

01:07:28.212 --> 01:07:29.146
[SIGHS]

01:07:29.813 --> 01:07:32.182
Seriously? You're still holding
on to that?

01:07:32.782 --> 01:07:33.717
It's what we do.

01:07:34.684 --> 01:07:36.086
It's what we did.

01:07:36.653 --> 01:07:37.821
PHOENIX:
There's only three of us.

01:07:38.522 --> 01:07:40.224
Pretty sure you know
how the vote turns out.

01:07:41.358 --> 01:07:42.326
Please.

01:07:44.128 --> 01:07:45.129
Just one last time.

01:07:46.530 --> 01:07:47.564
Okay.

01:07:48.732 --> 01:07:50.400
All those in favor of an escape.

01:07:54.604 --> 01:07:55.639
Well, that's it, then.

01:07:59.876 --> 01:08:00.977
PHOENIX: Did you find the wires?

01:08:03.079 --> 01:08:03.947
Yeah.

01:08:06.183 --> 01:08:07.151
Let's do this.

01:08:26.536 --> 01:08:28.604
[ALARMS BLARING]

01:08:36.412 --> 01:08:37.881
Well, it did something.

01:08:40.216 --> 01:08:41.285
I'm gonna try the door.

01:08:48.892 --> 01:08:49.859
I'm going up.

01:08:50.894 --> 01:08:51.995
No, Phoenix, wait!

01:09:04.640 --> 01:09:05.675
I'll find you...

01:09:06.643 --> 01:09:07.611
no matter what.

01:09:12.081 --> 01:09:13.216
I love you, Phoenix.

01:09:16.152 --> 01:09:17.321
I love you, too.

01:10:19.883 --> 01:10:21.150
-[CLICKS]
-[GASPS]

01:10:25.689 --> 01:10:27.757
[SCRAPES]

01:10:39.002 --> 01:10:40.737
-[DOOR SQUEAKING]
-[DOOR CLOSING]

01:11:15.071 --> 01:11:16.139
You're here.

01:11:19.208 --> 01:11:20.344
Is this real?

01:11:21.978 --> 01:11:23.079
I'm...

01:11:35.258 --> 01:11:37.093
-[WHISPERS] Oh, this is real.
-[LAUGHS]

01:12:04.187 --> 01:12:06.523
[SIGHS] This feels like a dream.

01:12:10.026 --> 01:12:11.961
BOSTON: If this was a dream,
I wouldn't be here.

01:12:16.500 --> 01:12:17.367
Yeah.

01:12:18.535 --> 01:12:19.536
Hi.

01:12:26.443 --> 01:12:27.811
You're taller than I expected.

01:12:32.949 --> 01:12:34.317
How did we wind up next
to each other?

01:12:34.751 --> 01:12:35.685
I don't know.

01:12:36.586 --> 01:12:37.621
I don't know either.

01:12:38.755 --> 01:12:40.189
DENVER: I don't remember
this place.

01:12:44.027 --> 01:12:45.028
PHOENIX: Fifty-seven.

01:13:00.143 --> 01:13:01.077
I mean,
maybe they moved us.

01:13:01.210 --> 01:13:02.612
No, we would have known that.

01:13:04.681 --> 01:13:06.049
Maybe we were here all along.

01:13:15.759 --> 01:13:18.127
The others have
to be here somewhere, right?

01:13:20.664 --> 01:13:23.266
BOSTON: Yeah, I... I don't know.

01:13:26.269 --> 01:13:27.270
There.

01:14:44.447 --> 01:14:45.982
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

01:14:49.318 --> 01:14:51.988
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

01:14:55.992 --> 01:14:57.160
Oh, my God.

01:14:59.295 --> 01:15:00.296
Oh, my...

01:15:05.334 --> 01:15:06.469
BOSTON: [WHISPERING] Phoenix.

01:15:06.770 --> 01:15:09.172
Phoenix, come here.
Look over there.

01:15:21.718 --> 01:15:22.819
Get down.

01:15:27.156 --> 01:15:28.157
What are we gonna do?

01:15:28.725 --> 01:15:30.259
We gotta find a way to get out
of here.

01:15:30.493 --> 01:15:31.995
-No, I want answers.
-No, Phoenix,

01:15:32.161 --> 01:15:33.529
we need to find a way out.

01:15:39.002 --> 01:15:40.336
Someone knows what's going on.

01:15:40.469 --> 01:15:41.738
Look, I will distract them.

01:15:41.971 --> 01:15:43.039
Wait. What? Why?

01:15:43.506 --> 01:15:45.709
Because they are blocking
the only exit.

01:15:48.277 --> 01:15:49.345
Hey!

01:15:50.146 --> 01:15:51.180
Go.

01:15:56.653 --> 01:15:57.821
Wait, wait, wait.

01:15:58.387 --> 01:15:59.322
Okay.

01:16:25.915 --> 01:16:27.617
Phoenix, we shouldn't be here.

01:16:29.018 --> 01:16:30.119
We need to go.

01:16:32.421 --> 01:16:34.057
Not until I know
what this place is.

01:16:49.773 --> 01:16:50.907
Look.

01:17:04.788 --> 01:17:05.789
There.

01:17:10.159 --> 01:17:11.761
DENVER: Phoenix,
you sure about this?

